Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large low sided wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed) and set aside 1 leaf per person (to put in your burger later). Halve the lettuce lengthways, then thinly slice widthways. Pop the sliced red onion into a small #bowl{} with the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, a pinch of @salt{} and the @sugar{1}(for the pickle). Mix well to combine and set aside. Slice the @halloumi{250%g} into 2 slices per person lengthways. Mix the @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @honey{15%g} together in a small bowl.

> The sugar is for the pickled red onion.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium high heat. When hot, add the @Vivera plant quarter pounder burgers{2} and fry until golden and crispy on both sides, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} and cover in #foil{} to stay warm. Wipe out the pan and return to the heat.

Lay the halloumi in the pan and cook until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. Once golden, add the smoked paprika and honey mixture, turning the halloumi to coat it in the glaze. Remove the pan from the heat.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2} and pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}. In a small bowl combine the @mayonnaise{1} with half the @chipotle paste{20%g}, mix well. Pop the sliced baby gem into a bowl with the remaining chipotle paste, a drizzle of @olive oil{} and 3/4 of the pickled red onion. Mix well to combine and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop a burger bun on each plate, spread the chipotle mayo on the base and top with a Vivera burger. Share the glazed halloumi on the burger and top with the remaining pickled red onion and reserved baby gem leaf. Share the wedges alongside with the salad. Enjoy!